    <section class="about">
      <header class="about-header">
        <h1>Our Story</h1>
        <p>How our community came to be and what we stand for.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="about-content">
        <section class="story">
          <h2>Our Story</h2>
          <p>
            Welcome to our community for book lovers! Our journey began with a
            simple idea: to create a space where passionate readers could
            connect, share their love for books, and discover new literary
            treasures. From humble beginnings, we've grown into a vibrant
            community of readers who support each other in our reading journeys.
            Whether you're looking for recommendations, joining a book club, or
            just chatting about your favorite authors, you're in the right
            place.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="team">
          <h2>Our Team</h2>
          <p>
            Behind this platform is a team of book lovers dedicated to fostering
            a warm, inclusive space for readers of all kinds. We believe that
            books have the power to connect people and open minds. Here are the
            faces behind the community:
          </p>
          <div class="team-members">
            <div class="team-member">
               
              <p><strong>  Ruan Le Roux</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class="team-member">
              
              <p><strong>Gerald Enright</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class="team-member">
              <p><strong>Masoho Keletso Andries</strong> </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="values">
          <h2>Our Values</h2>
          <p>
            We stand for inclusivity, respect, and a shared passion for reading.
            Our community encourages open and respectful discussions, with
            members supporting one another in their love for literature. We
            believe in creating a space where everyone feels welcome, regardless
            of their background or reading preferences. Join us in celebrating
            the power of books to unite and inspire.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>

